Hip Thrust (Barbell)
This exercise focuses the load on the gluteal muscles: Start seated with your knees bent, feet slightly wider than hip-distance apart: The toes can be turned out slightly if needed. The upper back (lower scapula) should be resting against the edge of the bench and in its center: Place the bar across the hips (into the crease of your hips): Squeeze the Glutes and press the bar straight up until the hips are aligned with the shoulders and knees, so the bench supports the mid-scapula area: Keep the core tight and maintain a slight chin tuck with your gaze to your body (a few inches above the bar): Slowly lower the bar until the hips arejust a few inches off the floor:
